==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stubble
<hw>Stub"ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>stobil</ets>, <ets>stoble</ets>, OF. <ets>estouble</ets>,
<ets>estuble</ets>, F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧tuele</ets>, LL. <ets>stupla</ets>,
<ets>stupula</ets>, L. <ets>stipula</ets> stubble, stalk; cf. D. & G.
<ets>stopped</ets>, OHG. <ets>stupfila</ets>. Cf.
<er>Stipule</er>.]</ety> <def>The stumps of wheat, rye, barley, oats, or
buckwheat, left in the ground; the part of the stalk left by the scythe
or sickle.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧After the first crop is off, they plow in the
wheast <xex>stubble</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Mortimer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Stubble goose</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the
graylag goose.</cd> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark> <au>Chaucer.</au> --
<col><b>Stubble rake</b></col>, <cd>a rake with long teeth for gleaning
in stubble.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stubbled</ent>⟦br⟧
